  "prompt": "Why did Quora limit question details to 300 words?",
  "response": "Quora likely limited question details to 300 words to encourage conciseness and clarity. By constraining the length, users are prompted to focus on the most essential aspects of their queries, making it easier for others to understand and respond effectively. Additionally, this limitation helps maintain the platform's overall readability and ensures that discussions remain focused and on-topic. Keeping content succinct also helps in better moderation and reduces the chances of lengthy, meandering descriptions that can complicate discussions or dilute the quality of responses.",
